Course Summary

This practice and study guide is designed to prepare you for the Ohio Assessments for Educators - Mathematics examination. The video lessons and quizzes reinforce key mathematics concepts in preparation for taking the teacher certification test.

About This Course

The Ohio Assessments for Educators (OAE) Mathematics study guide course covers information that can help you pass this teacher certification assessment. You can re-examine what you've already learned about real numbers and ratios as well as matrix operations and determinants, and the course lessons provide opportunities to review parallel lines, quadrilaterals, linear equations and triangle theorems. The course contains short and entertaining lessons that are all taught by expert math instructors. You'll also be able to take practice quizzes that are designed to strengthen the math skills you'll need to demonstrate on the exam. The course is accessible 24/7, and you can submit questions to our subject-matter experts if you need any extra help with the course material.

Check out our OAE test prep materials! We've got OAE courses to teach you the material, comprehensive OAE study guides to help you study, OAE practice tests to test your knowledge, and informational OAE resources to get you up to speed on testing logistics.

Syllabus & Course Information

This course goes over the topics that appear on the OAE Mathematics assessment, which will test your ability to understand number theory, relations and functions, mathematical problem solving, mathematical communication, trigonometric functions and more. When you're finished working through this course, you should be able to:

  • Work with fractions, percents and decimals
  • Understand proportions and units of measurement
  • Use logic and reasoning in math
  • Perform vector operations and work with exponents and exponential expressions
  • Interpret algebraic expressions, polynomials and inequalities
  • Differentiate between rational and radical expressions
  • Solve absolute value problems, quadratic equations and systems of equations
  • Define the elements of complex numbers, piecewise functions and logarithmic functions
  • Recognize continuity of functions, limits, rates of change and derivatives
  • Evaluate geometry and trigonometric functions
  • Comprehend the fundamentals of statistics and probability

Course Format

In this course, you'll study 406 lessons that are broken into 55 chapters. Our lessons are designed to be short, entertaining and simple so you can quickly review the material and remember important math formulas, concepts and terms. Be sure to take the accompanying self-assessments to practice applying your math skills.

OAE Mathematics (027) Exam Information

The purpose of the Ohio Assessments for Educators - Mathematics examination is to gauge your competency as an educator in a number of mathematical areas.

  • Number of Questions: 150
  • Question Type: Multiple-choice
  • Time Limit: 4 hours and 15 minutes
  • Exam Cost: $105

Preparing & Registering for the Ohio Assessments for Educators - Mathematics Examination

The video lessons in this Ohio Assessments for Educators - Mathematics examination course aim to refresh your knowledge of the topics that are included in the actual examination. They could also consist of new mathematics information that you haven't previously studied. Topics such as applications of integration, area under the curve and proofs are explored in the lessons.

You can register online for the examination on the Ohio Assessments for Educators website. Testing opportunities are offered throughout the year, Monday through Saturday by appointment. The website allows you to access test centers to check for seat availability. Just select the test you will be taking from the menu to begin the registration process.

Scoring the Ohio Assessments for Educators - Mathematics Examination

You will need a score of 220 to successfully pass the Ohio Assessments for Educators - Mathematics examination. Scores for this test are released once a month, and you'll typically receive your scores a few weeks after having taken the examination. You may elect to have your scores sent to your e-mail address or receive them in your account.

Mathematical Processes and Number Sense

Number of questions: 28-29

This section of the Ohio Assessments for Educators - Mathematics examination will test your ability to solve math problems. For example, it will make sure you understand how to analyze the use of estimation, solve math problems with rational numbers, percents and decimals, and solve real-world problems with proportions and ratios.

Patterns, Algebra and Functions

Number of questions: 36

This portion of the examination assesses your competencies with functions and relations. In part, the test will determine your ability to perform operations with functions and interpret representations of functions.

Measurement and Geometry

Number of questions: 28-29

You will demonstrate your ability to solve measurement problems in this portion of the examination. It focuses on Euclidian geometry and the applications of the Pythagorean theorem.

Trigonometry and Calculus

Number of questions: 28-29

Your ability to apply trigonometric functions to solve problems that include unit circles, angles and distance is assessed in this examination section. It also tests your knowledge of differential calculus.

Statistics, Probability, and Discrete Mathematics

Number of questions: 28-29

In this section of the examination, you can showcase your knowledge of discrete mathematics and statistics as well as your ability to calculate probabilities. This portion of the test will ensure that you know how to analyze data, series and sequences.
